title: For Sale:  Classic Interarms Walter PPK w/box and 3 mags
postcontent:
For sale we have a very nice classic Interarms Walther PPK .380 pistol, with box, papers, and a total of three (3) Walther factory magazines. If you are an older shooter, you may recognize the PPK as the gun made famous by James Bond in books and movies. This pistol, made in the mid-90's, is the much more desireable and collectible version imported for decades by Interarms, not the current production made by Smith and Wesson. This is also the scarce PPK model, NOT the PPK/S which is much more common and is a larger pistol. The PPK design dates from about 1929, with the PPK being placed in service in 1935. It was the first commercially successful double action autopistol, and is a "must have" for any pistol collector. It also makes a fine concealed carry firearm as well.
This pistol can be seen and purchased by appointment at my office just outside of Homestead. Please feel free to contact me with any questions you may have. I will entertain best offers, or full/partial trades for other firearms of equivalent quality. All laws will be complied with in this sale. Thanks for looking at my listing.Note - Due to the collectible nature of this firearm, I will consider shipping it to your FFL. However, since the vast majority of people who request shipping on Armslist are scammers, expect me to be suspicious until I know exactly who you are. If you are not willing to give me full information including a phone number so that we can talk, and provide me with an FFL I can contact who knows who you are, please don't waste my time asking me to ship this gun to you.
